[:neighborhood:] [:neighborhoods:] [:neighborhood of:] [:neighborhoods of:]

Within a topological space $$X$$, we say that a set $$U \subseteq X$$ is a \i[neighborhood of] $$x_0 \in X$$ iff $$U$$ is open and $$x_0 \in U$$.

Note that use of the term "neighborhood" can differ by author!
